verbose_text: However, although a large proportion of the Raf-1 is deactivated via the PI3K / Akt pathway, active Raf-1 levels still remain high enough to fully activate ERK on its own if B-Raf were not present (see Additional file XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY, Figure S3); this is because the Raf-1 feed-forward loop is relatively weak, especially when compared to the SOS feedback loop.
